# Windows shells (cmd, Windows PowerShell 5.1) run these scripts, so force CRLF
# and treat them as text. The UTF-8 BOM on install.ps1 / uninstall.ps1 -- which
# Windows PowerShell 5.1 needs to parse their (formerly em-dash-bearing) content
# without mis-decoding it -- is file content and is preserved by git regardless
# of these rules. The scripts are now ASCII-only as well, and CI's
# `encoding-guard` job fails the build if either ever regresses to non-ASCII
# without a BOM. Belt, suspenders, and a second belt.
*.ps1   text eol=crlf
*.psd1  text eol=crlf
*.bat   text eol=crlf
*.cmd   text eol=crlf

# Binary assets: never normalize line endings.
*.zip   binary
*.pdf   binary
*.png   binary
*.ico   binary
